data.title: Lleyton Hewitt Player Profile and Biography
data.text:
bio: Hewitt is the best performed Australian tennis player in recet years. He was once ranked number one in the world, and has won two Grand Slam events. what you may not know:

Hewitt turned pro in 1998

Hewitt began dating fellow tennis pro Kim Clijsters after they met at the 2000 Australian Open; the couple became engaged in December 2003 but split in 2004.

He first played for Australia's Davis Cup team in 1999.

Hewitt competed at Sydney in the 2000 Summer Olympics.

His favorite band is Midnight Oil.

Favorite foods are a meat pie, chips and tomato sauce.

He is a passionate supporter of the Australia rules football team the Adelaide Crows. He played Aussie Rules until age 13, when he decided to pursue a career in tennis.
